-- Microsoft Says U.S. Stores Sold 426,000 Xbox Players in February
-- B y   R o b   G o l u m
-- 2012-03-08T23:26:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/microsoft-says-u-s-stores-sold-426-000-xbox-players-in-february.html
Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  said U.S. retailers
sold 426,000 Xbox game consoles in February, giving the company
more than 40 percent market share for the 12th straight month.  February spending on all Xbox products, including hardware,
software and accessories, totaled $383 million, Redmond,
Washington-based Microsoft said today in an e-mail, citing NPD
Group Inc. data.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Golum at 
 rgolum@bloomberg.net  